==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exudation
<hw>Ex`u*da"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
exuding; sweating; a discharge of humors, moisture, juice, or gum, as
through pores or incisions; also, the substance exuded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Resins, a class of proximate principles, existing in almost all
plants and appearing on the external surface of many of them in the form
of <qex>exudations</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Am. Cyc.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exude</ent>⟦br⟧
